Package: nlfitr
Type: Package
Title: Fitting models to nonlinear data
Version: 0.1.0
Author: TJ Murphy <medtjm@emory.edu>
Maintainer: TJ Murphy <medtjm@emory.edu>
Description: Nonlinear regression of biological data involves choosing a model to fit the data. Initial estimates of the model's parameters must be provided. Regression then optimizes the model fit by iteratively improving these parameter estimates. 
    This package simplifies nlme-based nonlinear regression in R by providing several functions with pre-specified model formulas and intuitive parameter values. 
    These functions focus on common hyperbolic stimulus-response (dose-response, binding) and exponential (growth, decay) phenomena observed in biological systems. 
    Each model has a companion function for simulating responses.
